 info--1\">Design professionals, manufacturers and brands must make important decisions and communications about color every day. PANTONE standard OLED screen <sup>&reg; </sup> Validated <sup><a href=\"https://www.asus.com/vn/content/asus-lumina-oled-laptop/#footnote-1\">first </a></sup>This means that the colors you see on the screen are accurate, true to every detail!</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content__info info--1\">\r\n<div class=\"content-col content-col-1\">\r\n<h3>Display world-leading motion clarity with a 120 Hz OLED screen</h3>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content-col content-col-2\">\r\n<div class=\"content__info info--1\">120 Hz refresh rate, 0.2 ms response time on OLED laptop displays give you an even richer experience beyond top-notch color and quality for all types of content, from gaming, Creativity, daily tasks, multimedia entertainment, all smoother than ever. Can only use the word excellent!</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content__info info--1\">\r\n<div class=\"content-col content-col-1\">\r\n<h3>Fastest response time on any laptop for crystal clear motion</h3>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content-col content-col-2\">\r\n<div class=\"content__info info--1\">With displays, response time is the time needed to convert colors: the faster the time, the smoother the motion is reproduced. The diagram below shows the color transition from orange to yellow. On the ASUS Lumina OLED display, this transition takes as little as 0.2 milliseconds, while on the LCD display, it can take up to 10 ms or longer. This makes a significant difference, because colors and images on OLED screens look accurate for most of the frame, while images on LCD screens can appear blurry during transitions. .</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content__info info--2\">ASUS Lumina OLED display has a 0.2 ms response time, the fastest on any laptop and 50 times faster <sup><a href=\"https://www.asus.com/vn/content/asus-lumina-oled-laptop/#footnote-4\">4 </a></sup>compared to the average LCD screen